{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_80","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented US-009 in the provider layer with adapter-centric canonical↔wire conversion and committed it.\n\n### What changed\n- Added explicit `OpenAiCompatAdapter` implementing `LlmClient` and routed OpenRouter/Zhipu/LlamaCpp adapters through it.\n- Kept `AnthropicAdapter` on `LlmClient` and strengthened conversion behavior in Anthropic/OpenAI compat clients.\n- Added stop-reason mapping for tool usage:\n  - OpenAI `tool_calls` ↔ Anthropic `tool_use`.\n- Added bidirectional tool schema conversion helpers in compat conversion:\n  - Anthropic tool schema ↔ OpenAI function schema.\n- Improved HTTP error mapping inside adapters:\n  - `401/403 -> AuthError`\n  - `429 -> RateLimited` with `retry-after` extraction (seconds -> ms)\n  - `413` and `400` (when body indicates oversized request) -> `RequestTooLarge`\n  - timeout -> `Timeout`\n  - malformed JSON response -> `InvalidResponse` (already enforced, retained)\n- Refactored stream chunk/event conversion into helper logic and added ordering tests for:\n  - Anthropic SSE -> canonical stream events\n  - OpenAI SSE -> canonical stream events\n\n### Validation run\n- `cargo fmt --check` ✅\n- `cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings` ✅\n- `cargo test --workspace` ✅\n\n### Commit\n- `3b359dd`\n- Message: `feat: US-009 - Provider adapter triple conversion`\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}}
